# Repository Hygiene

## Common Remnant Patterns

### Build Directory Duplicates

macOS Finder copy operations can create `target 2/`, `target 3/` etc:

```bash
# Check for duplicates
ls -la | grep "target"

# Clean up (500MB+ each)
rm -rf "target 2" "target 3"
```

**Prevention**: `.gitignore` should include:
```gitignore
/target
/target */
target*/
```

### Debug HTML Artifacts

Debug visualizations at repo root:
```bash
# Find and clean
ls *.html 2>/dev/null
rm -f *_debug.html *_preview*.html
```

**Prevention**: `.gitignore` includes `*.html` with `!docs/**/*.html` exception.

### Test Artifacts

Directories matching `test_*` pattern:
```bash
# Check sizes
du -sh test_* 2>/dev/null

# Common culprits
rm -rf test_docs test_output test_screenshots
```

## Periodic Cleanup Check

Run monthly or before major commits:

```bash
# Size check
du -sh . target reports 2>/dev/null

# Find large untracked files
git status --short | grep "^??" | xargs -I {} du -sh {} 2>/dev/null | sort -h

# Find duplicate target dirs
ls -la | grep -E "target.*[0-9]"

# Find root-level artifacts
ls *.{html,png,jpg,txt} 2>/dev/null
```

## .gitignore Maintenance

### Essential Patterns for Rust NLP

```gitignore
# Build artifacts (including duplicates)
/target
/target */
target*/

# Generated HTML (keep docs)
*.html
!docs/**/*.html

# Test artifacts
test_*
!testdata/

# Reports (regenerated on demand)
reports/
*_report.md
*-report.md

# Python cache (from scripts/)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Model weights (large, downloaded on demand)
*.safetensors
*.onnx
*.bin
!tests/data/**  # Keep small test fixtures
```

### Common Mistakes

```gitignore
# BAD: Too broad, catches workspace crate
anno/

# GOOD: Only build artifacts
anno/target/

# BAD: Misses space in directory name
target2/

# GOOD: Catches "target 2", "target 3" etc
/target */
target*/
```

## Size Budget

| Directory | Expected | Alert If |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| `target/` | 5-10 GB | > 15 GB |
| `reports/` | < 1 MB | > 10 MB |
| `.git/` | < 100 MB | > 500 MB |
| Root files | < 1 MB | > 5 MB |

```bash
# Quick health check
du -sh target .git reports 2>/dev/null
```

## box-coref Experiment Hygiene

When working with `../box-coref`, experiment runs accumulate in `experiments/runs/`.

### Cleanup Commands

```bash
# Archive runs older than 7 days
cd ../box-coref && just archive-old-runs 7

# Delete "unknown_*" runs (from base.toml tests)
cd ../box-coref && just clean-unknown-runs

# Archive runs matching pattern
cd ../box-coref && just archive-pattern "base_*"
```

### .gitignore for Experiments

box-coref's `.gitignore` should include:
```gitignore
# Experiment runs (keep directory structure)
experiments/runs/*/
!experiments/runs/README.md

# Archive directory
experiments/archive/
```

### CI Verification

Before committing box-coref changes:
```bash
cd ../box-coref && just ci
```
